The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Helmet fine for driver
                                                                                                               Helmet fine for driver
          OUR LEGAL REPORTER                              
	Calcutta police have sent a notice to a high court lawyer asking him to pay a fine of Rs 100 for not wearing a helmet while driving his Maruti Omni on April 15 last year.        
	The notice, issued on July 30, 2008, reached Kallol Guhathakurta on April 30 this year.         
	You are directed to pay the amount within 15 days of receiving the letter and intimate it to the department immediately. If you fail to pay..., the case will be sent before an appropriate court..., the notice stated.        
	According to the notice, Guhathakurta was caught by traffic police on Karl Marx Sarani, under Kidderpore police station, on April 15, 2008, while driving the car (WB02S6742). The lawyer said he was not stopped by the cops and would not pay the fine. The officer-in-charge of the department could not be contacted.                                                                                                                                                                           
